<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-30T19:20:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-30T19:20:00-05:00" n="619" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d619">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi><note n="49" type="source" xml:id="d619fn49">Copy of telegram
                                obtained from the Franklin D. Roosevelt Library, Hyde Park,
                                N.Y.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-30T20:20:00-04:00">30 October 1943—8:20
                                    p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>310051. Personal for the Secretary of State. My 302232.<note n="50" xml:id="d619fn50">October 30, 6 p.m., <ref target="#pg_683">p.
                                    683</ref>.</note> Final disposition of all Italian ships should
                            apply to those used by British and Americans as well as to those used by
                            Russians.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>